items.name: Ultimate Art
items.description:
Suggestions

  • Use between 7 and 15 CFG Scale and between 25 and 50 Steps with Heun. Worse samplers might need more steps.

  • To reproduce my results you MIGHT have to change these settings:

    • Set "Do not make Heun deterministic across different batch sizes." (mostly for v1 examples)

    • USE HEUN as sampler

    • Set the ETA Noise Seed Delta (ENSD) to 31337

    • Set CLIP Skip to 2

    • DO not ENABLE face restore for portraits and close ups. It's terrible, messes up with eyes

  • Use simple prompts. Complex prompts might make less realistic pictures because of CLIP bleeding. More complex prompts does not mean better results. Keep it simple.

  • Use ADetailer to enhance faces in images having detailed background. Also don't forget to use Restore faces. Basically every solo portrait I made uses it. You can get my settings by clicking on "copy generation data". I suggest you use denoising under 0.3 to avoid getting always the same face.

items.name: HPS+
items.description:
Introduction

Are you tired of models that make too much sense, are too reliable, or have a clear purpose or application?
Me too.

Instructions For Use:

counterfeit v3 and counterfeit v3's easynegative would work with this model, but I do not habitually use negative prompts, and i didn't render my test images with counterfeit.

try like, typing some words into the text prompt and seeing what they do.
fusing this with a basemodel and training another lora on that would be very funny. someone should do that.

7/22/2023 update: I now specially recommend using the 'dynamic thresholding' addon for automatic1111's ui.

I like a 'mimic CFG scale' of 12,

a 'mimic scale scheduler' of 'linear up' with 4 'minimum mimic scale scheduler',

and a 'CFG scale scheduler' of 'half cosine down' with 4 'minimum CFG scale scheduler'.

Self attention guidance is good too, with values of 1.0 , 1.0.

Cautionaries And Caveats:

This lora is a synthesis of multiple other Loras made by unknown authors using unknown datasets made at the middle of the night & tested on '1girl' before release.

It could do literally anything.

This is a small project that has been in development for a long time. The initial goal was to expand the usage scenarios of the LORA "flowergirl." After several iterations, it was decided to integrate it into a CKPT for the convenience of beginners in their creative process.

Currently, in AI art generation, there is a prevalence of digital painting and thick paint techniques due to the nature of the datasets. However, after frequent use, aesthetic fatigue can set in. This model focuses on presenting a style with fine contour lines, aiming to simulate the traditional paper-based artistic style with smooth and concise strokes and clear outlines. Efforts have been made to convey a watercolor-like feeling in the background and clothing, reminiscent of traditional paper-based creations, in order to provide a different visual experience for users.

In the future, there may be considerations to further integrate modern oil painting styles. Your feedback and suggestions are welcomed as you use the model and provide your own artwork.

The pre-start, or first part, of the SuperMix1 mix.

Use the parameters that you find work best - some of the general use suggestions from SuperMix may apply to this model as well.

~20 steps, 7 scale, ~0.4 denoising, clip skip 1 or 2, is a good starting point

This model has some issues with detail accuracy, however just like SuperMix1 is primarily geared toward portrait styles. Keep in mind hands/anatomy may be a bit wild at times depending on your prompt and other parameter factors.

  • SUGGESTED PROMPT: (best quality, masterpiece, perfect face)¬†YOUR PROMPT, (hyper realism, soft light, dramatic light, sharp, HDR)

  • MY FAVORITE PROMPT: (best quality, masterpiece, perfect face, beautiful and aesthetic:1.2, colorful, dynamic angle, highest detailed face) YOUR PROMPT (official art, extreme detailed, highest detailed)

modelVersions.name: Aniverse V1.3 - Pruned
modelVersions.description:
About this version

Hi people!
I've a lot to say about this new version, and I really hope to remember all, eventually I'll modify in the future this change note.

First of all, this is a new total training, but merged with previous version of Aniverse, you'll understand why later.

I've do the training training to push at the limit of Stable Diffusion 1.5 (and my poor PC)
This model is trained at 1024x1024 pixel (the models before was at 768x768).
It was great, but to much "artefacts" at low resolution, so I preferred to do a merge with Aniverse 1.2.

I think the result is very good, but you'll decide, I really hope that you like it.
You don't need any more use the option HiRes.Fix (until a certain resolution, I saw that at 1280x720 it still work good, you can push at 1366x768 but sometimes it give you some problems).
Usually I use 512x904 and Adetailer, after when if I got a good image, I put it in 4x Ultrasharp tool

In model description I changed a little bit the Positive and Negative prompt, so check it out :)

Question: Now... why I put in "early preview" my model?

Answer:

  • Because I spent over 650 hours of training ( I don't remember if 20 or 22 days), and I hope that you can support me using my Ko-Fi page, where you can "buy" the new model. (if you have already a subscription in civitai, you can download it from here, I don't want that you pay twice)

  • For give to my supporters a "plus" to try the new models before the others.

I really hope that you can understand that I'm not looking to become "rich" selling my model, but I'm trying to figurate out how to pay the electricity bill :), nothing else.

So if you don't want be a my supporter, no problem, really :), wait only a couple of days more, to download the new version.

Enjoy!

Yujiro Hanma from the Series Baki the grappler. This is my final version of this lora but my next planned Lora as probably: Pickle, Jack, Baki, then Retsu

I reccomend using a strength of 1 for the latest model, you can lower it down to .6 if you want but it looks most Yujiro-Like at 1

Spent awhile but I reccomend looking over my photos and uploading your own, tested the flexibility of this lora massively with the photo variety

Much Easier to get the Demon back, almost shows up every time, and made it look much more like Yujiro

Weight of .7-1 but I stayed near 1

If you want a different outfit put "(((black shirt))), (((black pants)))" in the negative prompt and heavy emphasis on the outfit in positive prompt, Yujiro having one outfit made it hard to give a more diverse wardrobe

To get Demon Back:"From behind, shirtless" should work

items.name: Hugh Jackman in "The Prestige" (2006)
items.description:
You can support me here to be able to render better models (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Supporters can request model.

You can also support me and get exclusive models on my Patreon.

The Prestige is a 2006 psychological thriller film directed by Christopher Nolan, written by Nolan and his brother Jonathan and based on the 1995 novel by Christopher Priest. It stars Hugh Jackman as Robert Angier and Christian Bale as Alfred Borden, rival stage magicians in Victorian London who feud over a perfect teleportation trick.

Prompt : Prestige, realistic, natural lighting, post-processing, ultra realistic, highly detailed, very detailed, cinematic, hyper realistic, intricate scenery, sharp, photo by Annie Leibovitz, film, studio lighting, detailed skin, ultra realistic, bokeh, sharp features <lora:Prestige:0.8>

Negative prompt: (deformed iris, deformed pupils, semi-realistic, cgi, 3d, render, sketch, cartoon, drawing, anime, mutated hands and fingers:1.4), (deformed, distorted, disfigured:1.3), poorly drawn, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, extra limb, missing limb, floating limbs, disconnected limbs, mutation, mutated, ugly, disgusting, amputation

Steps: 50, Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, CFG scale: 12, Seed: -1, Face restoration: GFPGAN, Size: 768x1024, Model hash: 81086e2b3f, Model: realisticVisionV20_v20

Face restoration is optional, may provide better result if not activated.

Use Prestige as trigger.

items.name: RPGYeoman
items.description:
This is a LoRA for creating chainmail/ring mail style guards for medieval rpgs. The other RPGGuard and RPGDefender LoRAs really had bits of plate mail in all of the images regardless of how you specified them, so this RPGYeoman is to provide more of the chainmail / padded armor look instead.

The images were all upscaled using hires.fx upscaler 2, denoising 0.28, 4x_foolhard_Remacri upscaler.

The following trigger words work with RPGYeoman:

1boy, 1girl, bald, beard, belt, black hair, blonde hair, blue eyes, blurry, blurry background, boots, braid, breastplate, breasts, brown hair, brown pants, cape, chainmail, cleavage, closed mouth, dagger, dark skin, depth of field, facial hair, facial mark, fingerless gloves, freckles, full body, gauntlets, gloves, green eyes, helmet, holding, holding knife, holding sword, holding weapon, hood, jewelry, knife, lips, long hair, long sleeves, looking at viewer, looking to the side, male focus, medium breasts, mole, mustache, necklace, orange hair, own hands together, pauldrons, polearm, rain, realistic, red hair, ring, ring mail, robe, scabbard, scar, sheath, sheathed, shirt, short hair, shoulder armor, sitting, solo, solo focus, spear, staff, standing, strap, sunlight, sword, tattoo, twin braids, upper body, vambraces, wavy hair, weapon, yeoman

Logan is a 2017 American superhero film starring Hugh Jackman as the titular character. It is the tenth film in the X-Men film series and the third and final installment in the Wolverine trilogy following X-Men Origins: Wolverine (2009) and The Wolverine (2013). The film, which takes inspiration from the "Old Man Logan" comics storyline by Mark Millar and Steve McNiven, follows an aged Wolverine and an extremely ill Charles Xavier who defends a young mutant named Laura from the villainous Reavers led by Donald Pierce and Zander Rice.
